The paper deals with graph modification problems, specifically Trivially Perfect Editing, Trivially Perfect Completion, and Trivially Perfect Deletion. These problems are related to graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the study of kernelization complexity, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper mentions the Exponential Time Hypothesis, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
